    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "fresh air doesnt really change the fact that i'm just a profile picture to everyone. honestly. even if i did go for a walk, i'm just walking through a city of people who don't see me. it's like i've already disappeared, you know? it feels more like i'm just waiting for the rest of me to catch up to that feeling. like, what's the point of fighting to stay visible when there's nothing actually there to see?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
